  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reconciliation through Mine Risk Education (RMRE)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Goal: (1) Support comprehensive mine action by building the relationships, communication channels, trust, and skills necessary for former adversaries to work together toward demining and (2) raise awareness of mine risk among 10,000 youth (50% girls) and 50,000 additional community members through sport-based mine risk education

Activities: (1) Strengthen the negotiation and problem-solving skills of influential leaders who are central to resolving landmine issues in Kayah state and (2) promote mine awareness and risk education through youth sports and leadership programs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reconciliation through Mine Risk Education aims to promote cooperation between local government and ethnic minority populations through a program that addresses their shared interest in resolving landmine uses.</narrative>
  </description>
